{"title_page": "Vammala", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Vammala\n|official_name          = {{lang|fi|Vammalan kaupunki}}<br />{{lang|sv|Vammala stad}}\n|settlement_type        = Former town and municipality\n|image_shield           = Vammala.vaakuna.svg\n|image_map              = Vammala.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = 150px\n|map_caption            = Location of Vammala in [[Finland]]\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 150px\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Finland]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of Finland|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Pirkanmaa]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Sub-regions of Finland|Sub-region]]\n|subdivision_name2      = South Western Pirkanmaa sub-region\n|established_title      = [[Charter]]\n|established_date       = 1907\n|extinct_title          = Consolidated\n|extinct_date           = 2009\n|area_footnotes         = <ref name=\"total_area\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.maanmittauslaitos.fi/Pintaalat_kunnittain_1.1.2008.pdf |title= Area by municipality as of {{#time: j F Y|2008-01-01}} |accessdate= {{#time: j F Y|2010-04-13}} |publisher= Land Survey of Finland |format= PDF |language= Finnish, Swedish |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110807140011/http://www.maanmittauslaitos.fi/Pintaalat_kunnittain_1.1.2008.pdf |archivedate= 2011-08-07 }}</ref>\n|area_total_km2         = 876\n|area_land_km2          = 803.87\n|area_water_km2         = 72.13\n|population_as_of       = 2008-12-31\n|population_footnotes   = <ref name=\"population_count\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.vrk.fi/vrk/files.nsf/files/029EEED89C84611BC22575350052CE3A/$file/081231.html |title= Population by municipality as of {{#time: j F Y|2008-12-31}} |accessdate= {{#time: j F Y|2010-04-13}} |work= Population Information System |publisher= Population Register Center of Finland |language= Finnish, Swedish |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101202145510/http://vrk.fi/vrk/files.nsf/files/029EEED89C84611BC22575350052CE3A/%24file/081231.html |archivedate= 2010-12-02 }}</ref>\n|population_total       = 16635\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|demographics1_info1            = % (official)\n|demographics1_info2            = % \n|demographics1_info3            = % \n|demographics1_info4            = %\n|demographics_type2             = [[Demographics|Population by age]]\n|demographics2_title1           = 0 to 14\n|demographics2_info1            = 16.8%\n|demographics2_title2           = 15 to 64\n|demographics2_info2            = 61.6%\n|demographics2_title3           = 65 or older\n|demographics2_info3            = 21.6%\n|timezone               = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n|utc_offset             = +2\n|timezone_DST           = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +3\n|coordinates            = {{coord|61|20.5|N|022|54.5|E|region:FI|display=inline,title}}\n|postal_code_type       = Postal code\n}}\n'''Vammala''' is a [[List of former municipalities of Finland|former]] [[List of cities and towns in Finland|town]] and [[List of former municipalities of Finland|municipality]] of southwestern [[Finland]], chartered in 1907.\n\nOn 1 January 2009 Vammala was consolidated with the municipalities of [[Mouhij\u00e4rvi]] and [[\u00c4ets\u00e4]], to form a new city named '''[[Sastamala]]'''.\n\n==Geography==\nVammala was located in the southwest [[Pirkanmaa]] [[regions of Finland|region]], and was part of the former (1997 to 2010) [[provinces of Finland|province]] of [[Western Finland]].\n\n;Demographics\nThe municipality had a population of 16,635 (31 December 2008)<ref name=\"population_count\" /> and covered a land area of {{convert|803.87|km2|sqmi}}.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] was {{convert|20.29|PD/km2}}.\n\nThe municipality was unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\n[[Image:Tyrv\u00e4\u00e4n-vanha-kirkko.jpg|thumb|200|left|[[St. Olaf's Church in Tyrv\u00e4\u00e4]], near Vammala.]]\n{{clear|left}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[St. Olaf's Church in Tyrv\u00e4\u00e4]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Vammala}}\n*[http://www.vammala.fi/ Official Vammala website]\n\n{{Pirkanmaa}}\n\n[[Category:Sastamala]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Finland]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1907]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2009]]\n[[Category:2009 disestablishments in Finland]]\n{{WesternFinland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Vammala\n|official_name          = {{lang|fi|Vammalan kaupunki}}<br />{{lang|sv|Vammala stad}}\n|settlement_type        = Former town and municipality\n|image_shield           = Vammala.vaakuna.svg\n|image_map              = Vammala.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = 150px\n|map_caption            = Location of Vammala in [[Finland]]\n|pushpin_mapsize        = 150px\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Finland]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of Finland|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Pirkanmaa]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Sub-regions of Finland|Sub-region]]\n|subdivision_name2      = South Western Pirkanmaa sub-region\n|established_title      = [[Charter]]\n|established_date       = 1907\n|extinct_title          = Consolidated\n|extinct_date           = 2009\n|area_footnotes         = <ref name=\"total_area\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.maanmittauslaitos.fi/Pintaalat_kunnittain_1.1.2008.pdf |title= Area by municipality as of {{#time: j F Y|2008-01-01}} |accessdate= {{#time: j F Y|2010-04-13}} |publisher= Land Survey of Finland |format= PDF |language= Finnish, Swedish |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110807140011/http://www.maanmittauslaitos.fi/Pintaalat_kunnittain_1.1.2008.pdf |archivedate= 2011-08-07 }}</ref>\n|area_total_km2         = 876\n|area_land_km2          = 803.87\n|area_water_km2         = 72.13\n|population_as_