2010) [[provinces of Finland|province]] of [[Western Finland]].\n\n;Demographics\nThe municipality had a population of 16,635 (31 December 2008)<ref name=\"population_count\" /> and covered a land area of {{convert|803.87|km2|sqmi}}.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] was {{convert|20.29|PD/km2}}.\n\nThe municipality was unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\n[[Image:Tyrv\u00e4\u00e4n-vanha-kirkko.jpg|thumb|200|left|[[St. Olaf's Church in Tyrv\u00e4\u00e4]], near Vammala.]]\n{{clear|left}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[St. Olaf's Church in Tyrv\u00e4\u00e4]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Vammala}}\n*[http://www.vammala.fi/ Official Vammala website]\n\n{{Pirkanmaa}}\n\n[[Category:Sastamala]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Finland]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1907]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2009]]\n\n\n{{WesternFinland-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "Copying fromCategory:Populated places disestablished in 2009toCategory:2009 disestablishments in FinlandusingCat-a-lot", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vammala"}
