name            = \n|blank1_info            = \n|blank2_name            = \n|blank2_info            = \n|blank3_name            = \n|blank3_info            = \n|blank4_name            = \n|blank4_info            = \n|blank5_name            = \n|blank5_info            = \n|blank6_name            = \n|blank6_info            = \n|timezone               = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n|utc_offset             = +2\n|timezone_DST           = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +3\n|coordinates            = {{coord|65|02|N|026|09|E|region:FI|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_m            = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|area_code              = \n|website                = [http://www.ylikiiminki.fi/ www.ylikiiminki.fi]\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n'''Ylikiiminki''' ({{lang-sv|\u00d6verkiminge}}) is a [[List of former municipalities of Finland|former municipality]] of [[Finland]]. It was consolidated with the city of [[Oulu]] on 1 January 2009.\n\nIt was located in the [[provinces of Finland|province]] of [[Oulu (province)|Oulu]] and is part of the [[Northern Ostrobothnia]] [[regions of Finland|region]]. The municipality had a population of 3,512 (31 December 2008)<ref name=\"population count\" /> and covered a land area of {{convert|1040.66|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}.<ref name=\"total area\" /> The [[population density]] was {{convert|3.37|PD/km2}}. The municipality was unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\nNeighbour municipalities were Haukipudas, Kiiminki, Muhos, Oulu, Pudasj\u00e4rvi, Utaj\u00e4rvi and Yli-Ii. Oulujoki municipality that was closed in 1965 was also neighbour municipality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commonscat-inline}}\n* [http://www.ylikiiminki.fi/ Municipality of Ylikiiminki] \u2013 official site\n\n{{NorthernOstrobothnia}}\n\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Finland]]\n[[Category:Oulu|*Ylikiiminki]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1867]]\n[[Ca