anguage|Finnish]].\n\nIn May 2007 it was agreed that Ylistaro would merge with the city of Sein\u00e4joki and the neighbouring municipality of Nurmo; so from 2009 Ylistaro ended its independent existence.\n\n== External links ==\n{{commonscat-inline|Ylistaro}}\n\n{{SouthernOstrobothnia}}\n\n{{coord|62|56|25|N|22|31|00|E|region:FI_type:city(5582)_scale:50000|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2009]]\n[[Category:2009 disestablishments in Finland]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Finland]]\n[[Category:Sein\u00e4joki]]\n\n\n{{WesternFinland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = Ylistaro\n| official_name           = {{lang|fi|Ylistaron kunta}}<br />{{lang|sv|Ylistaro kommun}}\n| native_name             = <!-- if different from name -->\n| native_name_lang        = <!-- ISO 639-2 code. If more than one, use {{lang}} instead  -->\n| settlement_type         = [[Municipalities of Finland|Former municipality]]\n| image_skyline           = Ylistaron_kirkko_2010.jpg\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Ylistaro Church\n| image_flag              = \n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = \n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = Ylistaro.vaakuna.svg\n| shield_alt              = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = Ylistaro.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = <!-- Finland -->\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location within Finland\n| coordinates             = \n| coor_pinpoint           = \n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[Finland]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Provinces of Finland|Provi